The military truck market can be segmented based on various factors, including propulsion type, truck type, and application. When considering the propulsion type, military trucks are categorized into diesel, electric, hybrid, and gasoline-powered vehicles. In terms of truck type, they range from light utility vehicles to heavy utility vehicles, light multi-utility vehicles, armored personnel carriers, and logistics trucks. Furthermore, when looking at the application, military trucks serve purposes such as combat, transportation, communication, command & control, as well as rescue and recovery operations.

